==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oceanic
<hw>O`ce*an"ic</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧`sh⟦esl⟧*⟦acr⟧n"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>oc⟦eacute⟧anique</ets>. See
<er>Ocean</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the ocean;
found or formed in or about, or produced by, the ocean; frequenting the
ocean, especially mid-ocean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Petrels are the most aerial and <qex>oceanic</qex> of birds.</q>
<rj><qau>Darwin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to Oceania or its
inhabitants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oceanica</ent>⟦br⟧
